Description.enUS:
Warrior Hero, adept at summoning beasts and rallying his allies. Can learn Summon Bear, Summon Quilbeast, Battle Roar, and Stampede.

Attacks land and air units.

Cunning Hero, adept at quickly killing individual units and creating confusion among enemies. Can learn Mirror Image, Wind Walk, Critical Strike and Bladestorm.

Attacks land units.

Mystical Hero, effective at ranged attacks and scouting. Can learn Chain Lightning, Far Sight, Feral Spirit and Earthquake.

Attacks land and air units.

Cunning Hero, adept at healing magics and voodoo curses. Can learn Healing Wave, Hex, Serpent Ward and Big Bad Voodoo.

Attacks land and air units.

Warrior Hero, exceptional at absorbing damage and melee combat. Can learn Shockwave, War Stomp, Endurance Aura and Reincarnation.

Attacks land units.
A sturdy transport ship capable of carrying units over the sea.

Long-range siege weaponry. Effective against buildings but slow and vulnerable. Can learn the Burning Oil ability.

Attacks land units and trees.

A versatile attack ship good at destroying air attackers.

Attacks land and air units.

Supporting spellcaster. Can initially cast Sentry Ward, which summons an invisible detector. Can also learn Stasis Trap and Healing Ward.

Attacks land and air units.

Brutish Orc warrior. Can learn Berserker Strength.

Attacks land units.

Versatile spear-thrower, effective against air units. Can learn Troll Regeneration. Can be upgraded to Troll Berserker, which has the Berserk ability.

Attacks land and air units.

Lumbering war beast, mounted by an Orcish drummer. Has the abilities War Drums, and Devour. War Drums gives friendly units nearby a bonus to attack damage. Devour allows the Kodo to eat a target enemy unit. Can gain the War Drums Upgrade.

Attacks land and air units.

Basic worker unit. Can harvest gold and lumber, build structures, and Repair. Can also go inside Orc Burrows to give it an attack.

Attacks land units and trees.
Primary structure, used to train Peons and receive gathered resources. Can be upgraded to Stronghold and then Fortress to enable the production of additional types of structures and units.
Upgrade to Stronghold to enable the production of additional types of structures and units.
Upgrade to Fortress to enable the production of additional types of structures and units.

Spellcaster production building. Trains Shaman, Witch Doctors, and Spirit Walkers.
Also contains spell upgrades for Shaman, Witch Doctors, and Spirit Walkers.

Primary troop production building. Trains Grunts, Headhunters and Demolishers.
Also contains the Berserker Strength, Berserker, Troll Regeneration, and Burning Oil upgrades.
Summons Heroes. Revives slain Heroes.

Trains Raiders, Kodo Beasts, Troll Batriders, and Wind Riders.
Also contains the Ensnare, Envenomed Spears, Liquid Fire and War Drums upgrades.

Trains Tauren.
Also contains the Pulverize upgrade.

Provides food, which increases the maximum number of units that can be trained. Peons can garrison inside to attack enemy units. Can learn the Reinforced Defenses upgrade.

Attacks land and air units.

Serves as a drop-off point for harvested lumber.
Also contains upgrades for improved armor, melee weapons, ranged weapons, Reinforced Defenses, and Spiked Barricades.

Defensive structure. Can learn the Reinforced Defenses upgrade.

Attacks land and air units.
Creates a shop with purchasable items. The items available depend upon what level of upgrade your Great Hall has (Great Hall, Stronghold, or Fortress) and which buildings you have.

Highly mobile wolf rider. Effective against buildings. Can learn the Ensnare ability.

Attacks land units.

Primary spellcaster. Can initially cast Purge, which dispels magical buffs and can immobilize enemies. Can also learn Lightning Shield and Bloodlust.

Attacks land and air units.

Mystical Tauren caster. Has Ethereal Form, which allows him to avoid physical damage. Also has Spirit Link, which allows units to distribute incoming damage. Can learn Disenchant, and Ancestral Spirit.

Attacks land and air units.

Light flying unit with incredible perception. Good at destroying buildings. Has the Unstable Concoction ability, which allows the Troll Batrider to explode, dealing damage to nearby enemy air units. Can learn Liquid Fire, and Troll Regeneration.

Attacks land units.

Highly mobile flying creature. Excellent at scouting. Can learn Envenomed Spears.

Attacks land and air units.
